## A few things I think about a lot

**On CVEs and prioritisation** — NIST just announced that CVE submissions increased 263% between 2020 and 2025 and they can no longer enrich every submission. The industry has known for years that CVSS scores alone are a poor way to prioritise patching. Only 1% of CVEs ever get exploited in the wild. EPSS and KEV cross-referencing are how you find that 1%. I built this into SentinelIT before it became the official NIST model.

**On automation** — if I'm doing something manually for the third time, I write a script. Most of my best work has come from being irritated by a repetitive task.

**On industrial security** — OT/ICS is the most underprotected part of most enterprise environments. The tools that exist are either extremely expensive or extremely specialised. There's a real gap in the market for something that does IT and OT security in one platform without the £200k price tag.

